# status — human-facing rollup

Posted by the orchestrator at the close of every wave: one line per task
(done / blocked / gate-not-met) plus anything currently open. This is the
"are we on track at a glance" summary layer — the five per-agent
build.logs (plus orchestrator.log) remain the detailed record for when
you want to go deeper on any one line here. Newest entries at the bottom.
Do not delete or rewrite prior entries.

## 2026-07-04

- Tier 0 (Tasks 0.1/0.2/0.3): DONE — tester independently verified the exit
  gate. Backend: 4/4 pytest passed, ruff clean, mypy strict clean, /health
  boots. Frontend: ESLint/tsc clean, 1/1 Vitest passed, build succeeds,
  Vite shell serves. CONTRACTS.md and fixtures/ (pubmed/zotero/tokenizer)
  present and committed. See logs/tester.build.log for full detail.
- Adversarial review of Tier 0: DONE. Found and we fixed a real
  off-by-one bug in CONTRACTS.md's segmented-abstract worked example
  (char_end was 1 too long on two segments, contradicting the doc's own
  end-exclusive-slice invariant) — fixed in CONTRACTS.md. Flagged a
  tokenizer-corpus disambiguation note ("et al." vs. "Dr." splitting
  rules) forward to Task 1D/2D, no Tier 0 action needed. One apparent
  process-gate concern (tester log looked incomplete) turned out to be a
  stale read racing an in-flight log write — confirmed no real issue.
- Tier 0 exit gate: CONFIRMED MET (independently, by both tester and
  adversarial review) after the CONTRACTS.md fix above.

